@nisdas   We were punished jointly and severally for the situation you mentioned yesterday. There is a verifier 142525 in the network, and the block is not delivered on time in the 5306178 slot. https://mainnet.beaconcha.in/validator/142525#blocks 。 All verifiers who should have been in this slot (5306178) ATT will be punished.  

<img width="1106" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49090950/206443896-f6048689-149d-4cbf-86d1-9e63a38f7119.png">


Btw, how many validators are involved in this slot in total and how do I get this data, is it completely random? I want to make a whitelist for our own monitoring, if it is not our reason will no longer alert. If the block should have come out for me, but it didn't due to some kind of failure, is there a corresponding api to check?  Appreciated it !

Have the same issue, a similar environment with AWS + K8S, and also get random missed attestation. 
Trying to minimize the occurrence. 
@sdalmeida can you please share the chrony configuration you are currently using? 
@0xRook1e did you manage to solve or progress with your investigation? 

Thanks

@okorolov Sorry for the late reply, I didn't see your message.
I used to run a Cardano validator so I followed this Chrony setup. Just install chrony and use this config: https://github.com/Chris-Graffagnino/Jormungandr-for-Newbs/blob/master/docs/jormungandr_node_setup_guide.md#edit-etcchronychronyconf

To monitor my time skew, I used this Grafana dashboard: https://grafana.com/grafana/dashboards/7496-ntp/

@bert2002 I've brought down my missed attestation to around 1-2 a week by migrating my Beacon Node to an SSD. I also enabled [checkpoint sync](https://docs.prylabs.network/docs/prysm-usage/checkpoint-sync).
